```

Quick check (round your answers to four decimal places):

```{r q21}

question_numeric( "What is the relative frequency of 2 in the sample?",
                  answer(tabfr[2]/50, correct=TRUE),
                  correct = "Correct!",
                  incorrect = "Incorrect",
                  allow_retry = TRUE,
                  tolerance = 10^(-4)
)

```

```{r q22}

question_numeric( "What is the relative frequency of of a digit $\\geq 3$ in the sample?",
                  answer(sum(tabfr[3:9])/50, correct=TRUE),
                  correct = "Correct!",
                  incorrect = "Incorrect",
                  allow_retry = TRUE,
                  tolerance = 10^(-4)
)

```

If you wish, you can use the following chunk to compute the frequencies in the questions above using R:

```{r q21r, exercise=TRUE, exercise.eval=TRUE}

```

```{r q21r-hint}
